If you like all styles of beer, this place is great. If you like IPAs exclusively, there is potential for disappointment.  I can't speak with 100% certainty but the majority of their IPA selection is in cans and bottles and that presents a possible problem. You should understand that the longer an IPA sits in a can, the more the hopiness degrades. They may rotate frequently and go through them often enough, but that seems unlikely. If you're looking for an IPA it's entirely possible you won't get the best version of what you are ordering. Again, this is a caution and not something to take too seriously as I can not speak to their sales/rotation.  That being said, their selection for other styles is excellent. These other styles hold up much better over time and you should be able to get the best version of it.  For food I had the boneless Hot Honey BBQ wings. They were good, but the sauce was basically just a less sweet version of hot honey with almost no hint of traditional BBQ sauce. The sauce was not what I expected based on the title of it, but it was good enough nonetheless. The blue cheese I had served with it was more thin than what I'm traditionally used to but still had the marbled chunks associated with blue cheese. It's possible they cut it with something, I don't know and I hope that's not the case.  Overall I'm giving this 4/5 because the general beer selection is excellent, the food was good enough, and the service was great.
